Hello everybody, welcome to the first post on our new account. The intentions for this account is to spread awareness and create an environment to encourage discussion and hopefully make change. We will be discussing many topics affecting our everyday lives such as gender equality, sustainability and stigmatism around mental health.
For the first post I wanted to talk about the film ‚ÄòMoxie.‚Äô It actually inspired me to make this account. The film for me was inspiring as I saw a community develop and empower each other and it made me want to form this community. I think we can all make change in our own way and it does not have to be through speech making but in how you stand up for and support others. I loved the representation of feminism specifically the misconceptions around feminism (people believing that only women are feminists). I would love to address other misconceptions about feminism in another post! There have been criticisms of the film due to the under representation of Lucy‚Äôs character who combats issues around diversity and misogyny. I will be specifically focusing on intersectional feminism on my next post.Please comment if any of this film or other films you have watched have resonated with you and why. I would love to hear the responses! #feminism #feminist #moxie

This week Techila shot presents "Neuromorphic chip" .

As the name suggests, neuromorphic computing uses a model that's inspired by the workings of the brain. True, supercomputers make specific calculations at great speed, but the brain wins on adaptability. And with traditional models of computing struggling, harnessing techniques used by our brains could be the key to vastly more powerful computers in the future. Current generation AI tends to be heavily rules-based but neuromorphic systems are also likely to help develop better AIs as they're more comfortable with other types of problems like probabilistic computing, where systems have to cope with noisy and uncertain data.
